          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Bake the cakes, 12 to 15 minutes",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Heat the oven to 180°C fan. Line two 12-hole bun tins with paper cases. Beat the {{unsalted-butter}} and {{caster-sugar}} until pale and fluffy. Beat in the {{eggs}} one at a time, then the {{vanilla-extract}}. Fold in the {{plain-flour}} and {{baking-powder}}. Place a heaped teaspoon of batter into each case. Bake for 12 to 15 minutes until risen, golden, and springy to the touch. Cool in the tin for 5 minutes, then transfer to a rack to cool completely.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Ice with glacé icing",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For the ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "glacé icing",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termId": "cmpa6fnrq0000d8v4e8slj60o"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": ", sift the {{icing-sugar}} into a bowl and stir in the {{lemon-juice}} a tablespoon at a time until the icing falls from a spoon in a thick ribbon. Spoon a teaspoon onto each cake and spread lightly to the edges. Leave undisturbed for 20 minutes to set completely before storing.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
